{
  "_comment": "Shared audit/activity taxonomy: groups raw audit action verbs into the handful of activity types the panel filters by. Canonical mirror of Sources/ArgentUtilsCore/AuditCategory.swift (the Swift enum stays the source of truth for the exhaustive switch; this file lets the Linux front-end read the same taxonomy instead of re-hardcoding it). displayOrder = array order. title is shared; sfSymbol is the macOS icon, emoji the Linux icon; color is the macOS SwiftUI semantic name, colorHex the Linux/override default. actions maps each verb to a category id; unknown verbs fall through to `fallback`.",
